        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30059190-pooja?shelf=arc">arc</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1976868848" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1209398622581068504"><i>Has a heart of its own.</i><br/><br/><i>And that heart flutters, sometimes skips a beat or two, but reverts back to doing what it does the best - to fill with love and not blood.</i><br/><br/>Set apart in a league of its own, the story opens up with the life of three young children in the valley. The bonds of friendship and the sands of time alter like tides in a sea.<br/><br/>One thing remains constant - <i>The tree that bears a thousand apples.</i><br/><br/>It sees riots, murders, bloodshed. It stands it all. The tears water its roots.<br/><br/>I will not delv</span>
  <span id="freeText1209398622581068504" style="display:none"><i>Has a heart of its own.</i><br /><br /><i>And that heart flutters, sometimes skips a beat or two, but reverts back to doing what it does the best - to fill with love and not blood.</i><br /><br />Set apart in a league of its own, the story opens up with the life of three young children in the valley. The bonds of friendship and the sands of time alter like tides in a sea.<br /><br />One thing remains constant - <i>The tree that bears a thousand apples.</i><br /><br />It sees riots, murders, bloodshed. It stands it all. The tears water its roots.<br /><br />I will not delve deep into the plot as that is for you to find out. The blurb makes you interested and the initial pages are a treat. What follows is just sheer deftness of the writer at penning beautiful words to describe the events and the scenic beauty.<br /><br />Set amongst the real life scenario, this fictional piece of writing might just be what the bibliophile might like to read. The affectionate conversations turn into hostility and it is hard to choose one side from the other. And that is what the author does; laying out the emotions of the three friends. Their losses and their fears.<br /><br />The characters are well drawn and background aptly sketched. The plot puts all of them in a splendid mosaic and gives you the best end result.<br /><br /><i>Verdict : 5 Stars | Moving.</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="1209398622581068504" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


