<div id="review_2240771076" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2240771076" />
    <a title="Saumyata Bisht" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/72484489-saumyata-bisht"><img alt="Saumyata Bisht" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2240771076?book_show_action=true">Jan 03, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Saumyata Bisht" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Saumyata Bisht" href="/user/show/72484489-saumyata-bisht">Saumyata Bisht</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2240771076" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7394840955977564744">Sanchit Gupta as an Indian author is the most refreshing one I have read so far.<br/>KITE RUNNER OF INDIA. That&apos;s the best way I can describe this book.<br/>The kashmiriyat is so beautifully woven into the book that you will carry it with you after the book is finished.<br/>I liked the way the characters are designed and how tiny nuances are given the most beautiful form.<br/>Especially how the character of Safeena is described.<br/>The book is the best description of Kashmir that I have ever come across.<br/>As for the writ</span>
  <span id="freeText7394840955977564744" style="display:none">Sanchit Gupta as an Indian author is the most refreshing one I have read so far.<br />KITE RUNNER OF INDIA. That's the best way I can describe this book.<br />The kashmiriyat is so beautifully woven into the book that you will carry it with you after the book is finished.<br />I liked the way the characters are designed and how tiny nuances are given the most beautiful form.<br />Especially how the character of Safeena is described.<br />The book is the best description of Kashmir that I have ever come across.<br />As for the writing is concerned.The author has magic with words and he even makes the most tragic and sad parts riveting.<br />I am so happy that when most Indian authors go for college romances trying to copy west Sanchit Gupta talks about something that is truly Indian.I can see his name with big authors like Khaled Hosseini soon.A must read for anyone who wants to revel in the lovely bond of friendship and wants to encounter the harsh realities in India.Looking forward to reading his next work.<br />Big fan!!!!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="7394840955977564744" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


